# AC9d: AC6 — user rebinding of `if` disables narrowing (no false
# positives). The user binds their own `my-if` that always takes the true
# branch. Since `my-if` is a user-defined function (not the prelude's `if`),
# narrowing does NOT fire and the false branch body is type-checked normally
# without any narrowing context.
my-if(c, t, _f): t
` { type: "(number | string) → number" }
safe(x): my-if(x number?, x + 1, 0)

result: safe(42)
